GREATER CHINA DAYBOOK: April CPI; Hong Kong Exchanges, Tencent Earnings

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-10T23:35:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/greater-china-daybook-april-cpi-hong-kong-exchanges-tencent-earnings.html
China ’s inflation likely slowed to
5.2 percent last month from 5.4 percent in March, according to
the median estimate in a Bloomberg survey of 30 economists.  Producer price growth probably fell to 7 percent from 7.3
percent in March, and retail sales probably accelerated to 17.6
percent from 17.4 percent, according to a survey of 28 analysts.
China’s statistics bureau is scheduled to release inflation and
other economic data for April at 10 a.m. in Beijing today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephanie Wong at 
